# 📊 Network Usage Tracker

> A real-time desktop network monitoring application built using **Python**, **Tkinter**, and **Psutil** that tracks network usage, displays connection status, and provides bandwidth alerts through a clean graphical interface.

---

## 🚀 Overview

**Network Usage Tracker** is a lightweight desktop application designed to monitor system network activity in real time. It continuously tracks incoming and outgoing traffic, displays current usage, checks internet connectivity, and alerts the user when usage exceeds a defined limit.

This project demonstrates core concepts of:

* GUI development
* System monitoring
* Networking basics
* Real-time data processing in Python

---

## ✨ Features

* 📈 Real-time network usage tracking
* 🌐 Internet connectivity detection
* 🖥️ Local IP address display
* 🚨 Bandwidth limit alert system
* 🎨 Clean and user-friendly GUI
* ⚡ Live updates without freezing UI
* 🔄 Continuous monitoring loop
* 💻 Cross-platform compatibility

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

* Python 3
* Tkinter (GUI)
* Psutil (System monitoring)
* Socket (Network connectivity)
* Pillow (Image handling)

